The paper discusses the optimization of LSTM-RNN-based statistical parametric speech synthesis for deployment on mobile devices, which involves techniques related to signal processing, machine learning, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of robust inference and multi-frame inference, which are related to control and systems engineering, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
